      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The government may sue to\ndissolve the trust. Philip Stewart,\nlong opposed to the present regime,\nis likely instrumental in the\nmove. He recently conferred with\nRoosevelt.\n\n\nSenator Crowley, democrat, this\nmorning introduced a resolution\nasking the appointment of nine\nmembers to assist the government\nIn investigating the smelter trust\nand Simon Guggenheim's connec-\nton herewith.\n\n\nHe was defeated by party vote\nand record of the motion expunged.\nCrowley said he wanted to give the\nrepublicans chance to clear their\nskirts of sensational charges."
    }
